  "prompt": "How much did each actor get paid to star in The Avengers?",
  "response": "The salaries of the actors in *The Avengers* (2012) varied significantly based on their roles, fame, and negotiating power. Here\u2019s a rough breakdown of what some of the main cast members were reportedly paid:\n\n1. **Robert Downey Jr. (Iron Man)** - $50 million  \n   Robert Downey Jr. was the highest-paid actor in the film, earning a base salary of around $10 million plus a significant backend percentage of the movie's profits. This totaled approximately $50 million due to the film's massive success.\n\n2. **Chris Hemsworth (Thor)** - $150,000 to $200,000  \n   Chris Hemsworth, still relatively new to the role of Thor at the time, reportedly earned between $150,000 and $200,000 for his role in *The Avengers*.\n\n3. **Chris Evans (Captain America)** - $200,000 to $300,000  \n   Chris Evans, who had already appeared in *Captain America: The First Avenger*, earned a similar amount to Hemsworth, reportedly between $200,000 and $300,000.\n\n4. **Scarlett Johansson (Black Widow)** - $400,000 to $500,000  \n   Scarlett Johansson, who had a growing presence in Hollywood, earned a higher salary than Hemsworth and Evans, reportedly between $400,000 and $500,000.\n\n5. **Mark Ruffalo (Hulk)** - $2 million to $3 million  \n   Mark Ruffalo, who replaced Edward Norton as the Hulk, earned a higher salary, reportedly between $2 million and $3 million.\n\n6. **Jeremy Renner (Hawkeye)** - $2 million to $3 million  \n   Jeremy Renner, who played Hawkeye, earned a similar amount to Ruffalo, reportedly between $2 million and $3 million.\n\n7. **Samuel L. Jackson (Nick Fury)** - $4 million to $6 million  \n   Samuel L. Jackson, a veteran actor and recurring character in the MCU, earned significantly more, reportedly between $4 million and $6 million.\n\nThese figures are based on reports and estimates and may not be entirely accurate, as exact contract details are often kept private. Additionally, some actors may have negotiated backend deals or bonuses based on the film's performance. After *The Avengers*, many of the actors received substantial pay raises for subsequent Marvel films, especially Downey Jr., who continued to be a top earner in the franchise.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
